    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains two discrete time series (12 monthly observations) comparing inventory movements. Synthetic transaction counts show inverse patterns: purchases (\u03bc=6.75, \u03c3=1.60) maintain operational stock while sales (\u03bc=1.92, \u03c3=1.16) demonstrate irregular demand. The dotplot visualization maximizes data-ink ratio through position encoding (Tufte principle), using rectangular markers at integer positions to prevent false precision. Cairo's perceptual effectiveness is achieved through complementary colors (red=depletion, green=acquisition) and direct value labeling. Stacked markers maintain proportional spatial relationships while temporal alignment on the x-axis enables seasonal pattern recognition. Chart dimensions (800\u00d7400px) maintain 2:1 aspect ratio for optimal marker density without overlap."
